.ds n) explain_opendir_or_die
.cp 0  \" Solaris defaults to ''.cp 1'', sheesh.
.TH explain_opendir_or_die 3
.SH NAME
explain_opendir_or_die \- open a directory and report errors
.if require_index \{
.XX "explain_opendir_or_die(3)" \
    "open a directory and report errors"
.\}
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <libexplain/opendir.h>
.sp 0.3
DIR *explain_opendir_or_die(const char *pathname);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]explain_opendir_or_die\fP function is used to call the
\f[I]opendir\fP(3) system call.  On failure an explanation will be
printed to \f[I]stderr\fP, obtained from \f[I]explain_opendir\fP(3),
and then the process terminates by calling \f[CW]exit(EXIT_FAILURE)\fP.
.PP
This function is intended to be used in a fashion
similar to the following example:
.RS
.ft CW
.nf
DIR *dir = explain_opendir_or_die(pathname);
.fi
.ft R
.RE
.TP 8n
\f[I]pathname\fP
The pathname, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]opendir\fP(3) system call.
.TP 8n
Returns:
On success, a pointer to the directory stream.
On failure, prints an explanation and exits, does not return.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SH SEE ALSO
.TP 8n
\f[I]opendir\fP(3)
open a directory
.TP 8n
\f[I]explain_opendir\fP(3)
explain \f[I]opendir\fP(3) errors
.TP 8n
